dct_description_sm: From the latest information in the Hydrographic Department of the Admiralty ; Drawn by Edward J. Powell of the Hydrographic Office under the direction of Capt. Hoskyn, R.N. Supert. of Charts ; Engraved by Davies, Bryer & Co. ; Published at the Admiralty, 26th, Augt. 1872, under the Superintendence of Rear Admiral G. H. Richards, C.B. F.R.S., Hydrographer ; Sold by J. D. Potter Agent for the sale of the Admiralty Charts 145 Minories.
Hachure and spot-height relief with soundings showing depths.
Waterways, coasts, islands, low water areas, make-up of sea beds (such as sand, clay, ooze), railways (including unfinished), various topographical notes.
